The paper focuses on multi-choice reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also utilizes pre-trained language models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The matching network design used in multi-choice MRC is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
